<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Violence Averted San Bernardino County SWAT team members stormed a shed, 
above, outside a Bloomington home Monday, eight hours after a suspected drug 
manufacturer threatened to blow it up. The incident began before dawn with a 
report that bottles of ether had been delivered there. Deputies sealed off two 
blocks and evacuated six homes. SWAT team members used tear gas to enter the 
shed after a negotiating team failed to persuade the man to surrender. The 
unidentified suspect, below, was being held on suspicion of occupying a 
dwelling where narcotics were accumulated and sold. LARRY GUS 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
