<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: PUERTO RICAN BANK OKS FINANCING FOR HOH PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOH Water Technology said it has received approval in principle for $2 million 
in financing from Economic Development Bank of Puerto Rico. The financing is 
intended to help the fledgling Newbury Park company set up a manufacturing 
plant in Puerto Rico to manufacture its water purification systems for 
residential and commercial use. 
</P>
<P>
The financing is conditional until the consulting firm Arthur D. Little 
concludes its report on the market potential of HOH's products. That report is 
expected to be completed next month. 
</P>
<P>
If the financing is completed, Economic Development Bank would lend HOH $1.5 
million and invest $500,000 in the company. HOH has recently been suffering 
from a cash crunch. Company President David Kravitz said the company hopes to 
be in production within six months after receiving the financing. 
</P>
<P>
The Puerto Rican government often lends money to companies that locate 
factories there in an effort to create jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
