<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Connie Chung's agent said Monday she is "close" to making a decision about 
whether to stay at NBC (her contract expires in late May) or jump to CBS. 
Alfred Geller wouldn't hint at which way she's leaning, and muddied the 
speculative waters further by saying if she does go to CBS, she might not work 
on either "West 57th" or "60 Minutes." Rumors have circulated that she was 
headed for one or the other of those CBS magazine shows. CBS has yet to replace 
Diane Sawyer who left "60 Minutes" last month for a new job at ABC. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
</P>
