<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIVEN A CHOICE, THEY HAVE TO GO FOR THE TAR HEELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FELLENZER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When it comes to basketball, is North Carolina really the Tar Heel state? 
</P>
<P>
The answer, overwhelmingly, is yes. In this state, they do polls on subjects 
like that. 
</P>
<P>
Recently, a Chapel Hill marketing firm did a random telephone survey of 520 
adults, asking the following question: "If all of the following teams were 
playing on television at the same time, but not playing each other, which would 
you watch: Duke Blue Devils, N.C. State Wolfpack, Charlotte Hornets, Carolina 
Tar Heels or Wake Forest Demon Deacons?" 
</P>
<P>
The results: North Carolina, 34%; N.C. State, 19%; Charlotte and Duke, 12%, and 
Wake Forest, 3%. A total of 20% said they "don't know." 
</P>
<P>
The Tar Heels carried every region of the state except Charlotte, where the 
Hornets had a 32%-26% edge. JEFF FELLENZER 
</P>
</TEXT>
