<HEADLINE>
<P>
KELLY DEFENDS TITLE WITH KNOCKOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending champion Derrick Kelly scored an eighth-round knockout over Derwin 
Richards Monday night at the Forum to retain the North American Boxing 
Federation welterweight crown. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly, from Riverside, held an advantage throughout the scheduled 12-round bout 
with quick moves that confused Richards. 
</P>
<P>
Referee Lou Filippo stopped the bout at 2:15 of the eighth round as Richards, 
21, was unable to ward off Kelly, 28. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly (23-1-2) was expected to meet a difficult challenge from the NABF's No. 
10 contender. Kelly gained the NABF welterweight crown with a victory over Luis 
Santana of the Dominican Republic. 
</P>
<P>
In a semifinal match in the $225,000 Forum Superlightweight Tournament 
Championship, Rodolfo Aguilar of Panama City, won a unanimous 10-round decision 
over Joe Rivera of Rio Piedra, Puerto Rico. 
</P>
