MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KSLD-TV Channel 62, the first new TV station in the Los Angeles market in 
years, went on the air Monday night with programming supplied by Home Shopping 
Network, instead of Spanish-language programming as originally announced. 
Station president Jack Hodin said he made the change after he was unable to 
secure enough Spanish programs. "The group I had a prospective contract with 
was simply not prepared to get started," Hodin said. KSLD will broadcast from 9 
p.m.-6 a.m. until April 3, when it will increase to 24 hours daily. Hodin said 
his station's Home Shopping programming is "differently packaged and presented" 
than that carried on Channel 46. ALEENE MacMINN 
