<P>
WOMAN ADMITS KILLING MAN, NEW GIRLFRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman has pleaded guilty to second-degree murder for shooting her former 
lover and his girlfriend in their Panorama City apartment, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Charisse Lewis, 33, will be sentenced April 11 in Van Nuys Superior Court. She 
faces a sentence of 15 years to life in prison. 
</P>
<P>
She was arrested in October in Chicago after seeking treatment for sickle cell 
anemia, said Deputy Dist. Atty. Stephen Baron. Lewis fled after the July 17 
killings, and authorities alerted hospitals to notify them if she sought 
treatment. 
</P>
<P>
She was originally charged with first-degree murder in the deaths of Jewel 
Prude, 34, the man with whom she had lived for two years, and Shirley Marie 
Johnson, 35. Prosecutors agreed to allow Lewis to plead guilty to the lesser 
charge as part of a plea agreement. 
</P>
