<P>
YOUTH SENT TO PRISON FOR 17 YEARS IN SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A reputed gang member has been sentenced to 17 years in prison for the shooting 
death of a 10-year-old boy near Pacoima Park. 
</P>
<P>
Joaquin Garcia, 18, was also sentenced Friday to an additional three years in 
prison for possession of homemade knives found in his jail cell. 
</P>
<P>
A San Fernando Superior Court jury convicted Garcia in July in the fatal 
shooting of Alejandro Salazar. The child died after a ricocheting bullet struck 
him in the back of the head as he played with a group of children near Pacoima 
Park on July 19, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Garcia testified that he had fired his .25-caliber automatic pistol to scare 
away two rival gang members who he believed were beating up a 14-year-old 
friend. 
</P>
<P>
According to police, Garcia fired several shots in the direction of the gang 
members, one of which ricocheted off the street and struck Salazar. 
