</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 1,200 flight attendants with Continental Airlines, like Eastern 
Airlines a subsidiary of Texas Air Corp., have gone on strike, a union 
spokeswoman said today on the second day of a walkout. 
</P>
<P>
"We've had 1,207 flight attendants either walk off of aircraft or not show up 
for work. We're very encouraged," spokeswoman Myra Clayton said. "Those are not 
people who are sick or have days off." Continental has had to delay a number of 
flights, she said, and called in all its reserve employees. 
</P>
<P>
Continental, however, said in a statement that only about 2% of its 6,500 
flight attendants have responded to the call by the Union of Flight Attendants 
and said the action has had no effect on its operations. 
