<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
FINANCIAL NEWS CONSIDERS MERGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Financial News Network today announced it is considering various proposals to 
merge with other broadcast companies but had not forged any specific deal with 
Turner Broadcasting System Inc. 
</P>
<P>
FNN's parent company is Infotechnology Inc., which controls United Press 
International. 
</P>
<P>
In Atlanta, Turner spokesmen refused to comment on published reports that the 
giant cable network was set to buy a controlling interest in FNN for $100 
million, pending approval by the company's board of directors this week. But 
spokesmen for both Turner and FNN acknowledged that the two companies had 
entered into negotiations several months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
