<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ASTROS GET INFIELDER LOMBARDOZZI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KISSIMMEE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Houston acquired second baseman Steve Lombardozzi from the Minnesota Twins 
today for an Astros player to be named later, the Astros announced. 
</P>
<P>
Lombardozzi, 27, hit .209 in 103 games for the Twins last season and drove in 
27 runs. He led all hitters with a .412 average for the Twins in the 1987 World 
Series. The infielder has a .233 career average in three seasons with the 
Twins. 
</P>
<P>
Astros regular season baseman Bill Doran is recovering from arthroscopic knee 
surgery performed March 7. Doran suffered through a series of injuries last 
season, including back spasms and underwent off-season shoulder surgery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
