<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FLAMES' MARK HUNTER SUSPENDED FOR 3 GAMES FOR HITTING OPPONENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTREAL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Calgary Flames right wing Mark Hunter was suspended for three games without pay 
today for hitting New York Rangers defense man Michel Petit with his stick in a 
game March 13, the NHL announced. 
</P>
<P>
League Executive Vice President Brian O'Neill said Hunter "deliberately swung 
his stick at the back of his opponent and with sufficient force to cause him to 
fall to the ice. 
</P>
<P>
"Even though the blow did not result in serious injury, the player must be 
responsible for his actions." 
</P>
<P>
The suspension would take effect March 28 but can begin immediately if the 
Flames agree to waive the seven-day period in which an appeal may be filed. 
</P>
<P>
Hunter, 26, has 22 goals and eight assists in 62 games with Calgary this 
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
